external_knowledge:
Deployed models refer to models that are currently in use; 
Access count is a measure of how many times a model has been accessed within a given time frame;
Average accuracy and precision metrics are measures of how well a model performs in comparison to a standard.

sql:
SELECT MAX(timestamp) AS latest_timestamp
FROM model_performance_history
WHERE model_id = 0;

SELECT AVG(JSON_EXTRACT(performance_data, '$.accuracy')) AS average_accuracy
FROM model_performance_history
WHERE model_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Accuracy refers to the proportion of correct predictions made by a model; 
The 'JSON_EXTRACT' function is used to extract the value of a specific key from a JSON object; 
The '$.accuracy' parameter in 'JSON_EXTRACT' refers to the path to the 'accuracy' key in the JSON object.
